==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: iron lung
<hw>i"ron lung"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A steel chamber,
usually cylindrical, enclosing the entire body of a person except for
the head, used to assist respiration for people suffering from disease,
especially poliomyelitis. A reciprocating piston at the end causes
alternating high and low pressure inside, which forces or assists the
breathing of the patient within.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>iron maiden</ent>⟦br⟧
